Project Overview

This project analyzes global disaster data from 2018 to 2024 to understand the economic impact, 
human casualties, disaster frequency, and response efficiency across countries and disaster types. 
The analysis highlights high-loss years, costliest disasters, and disaster-prone regions, 
along with response and recovery patterns.


ğŸ¯ Objectives

Identify the year with the highest economic loss due to global disasters

Analyze economic loss and casualties by disaster type

Determine countries most frequently affected by disasters

Evaluate response time, recovery duration, and response efficiency

Assess severity patterns across disaster categories


