Disaster Count by Country

Response Efficiency Score by Country


ğŸ” Key Insights

Certain years experienced significantly higher economic losses, indicating periods of severe global impact.

Specific disaster types consistently caused maximum economic damage and casualties, making them high-severity risks.

Some countries faced frequent disaster occurrences, highlighting geographic vulnerability.

Response and recovery timelines varied by disaster type, revealing gaps in preparedness and recovery efficiency.

Countries with higher response efficiency scores demonstrated better disaster management outcomes.


